<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/6bd88c23354f3d1a5df318bea278c917.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 8 and b = 3. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>8.5</li><li>69.4</li><li>20.6</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={8}^{{2}}+{3}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={64}+{9}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={73}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{73}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.5440037453175}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.5}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{3}}\right)}}}\approx{69.443954780417}\approx{69.4}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{69.443954780417}^{\circ}\approx{20.556045219583}\approx{20.6}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

